"android-app://org.wikipedia/http/en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas"/>\n<link rel="alternate" type="application/x-wiki" title="Edit this page" href="/w/index.php?title=From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas&amp;action=edit"/>\n<link rel="edit" title="Edit this page" href="/w/index.php?title=From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas&amp;action=edit"/>\n<link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/static/apple-touch/wikipedia.png"/>\n<link rel="shortcut icon" href="/static/favicon/wikipedia.ico"/>\n<link rel="search" type="application/opensearchdescription+xml" href="/w/opensearch_desc.php" title="Wikipedia (en)"/>\n<link rel="EditURI" type="application/rsd+xml" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd"/>\n<link rel="license" href="//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/"/>\n<link rel="canonical" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas"/>\n<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//login.wikimedia.org"/>\n<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//meta.wikimedia.org" />\n<!--[if lt IE 9]><script src="/resources/lib/html5shiv/html5shiv.min.js"></script><![endif]-->\n</head>\n<body class="mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-0 ns-subject page-From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas rootpage-From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas skin-vector action-view">\t\t<div id="mw-page-base" class="noprint"></div>\n\t\t<div id="mw-head-base" class="noprint"></div>\n\t\t<div id="content" class="mw-body" role="main">\n\t\t\t<a id="top"></a>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="siteNotice" class="mw-body-content"><!-- CentralNotice --></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class="mw-indicators mw-body-content">\n<div id="mw-indicator-featured-star" class="mw-indicator"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Featured_articles" title="This is a featured article. Click here for more information."><img alt="This is a featured article. Click here for more information." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/20px-Cscr-featured.svg.png" width="20" height="19" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/30px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/40px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="462" data-file-height="438" /></a></div>\n</div>\n\t\t\t<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">From The Doctor to my son Thomas</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="contentSub"></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">\n\t\t\t\t\tJump to:\t\t\t\t\t<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, \t\t\t\t\t<a href="#p-search">search</a>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><table class="infobox vevent" style="width:22em">\n<tr>\n<th colspan="2" class="summary" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight: normal; background: #CCCCFF; padding: 0.25em 1em; line-height: 1.5em;">"<b>From The Doctor to my son Thomas</b>"</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas.jpg" class="image" title="Peter Capaldi looking at camera"><img alt="Peter Capaldi looking at camera" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b0/From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas.jpg/220px-From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas.jpg" width="220" height="124" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b0/From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas.jpg/330px-From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/b/b0/From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas.jpg 2x" data-file-width="421" data-file-height="237" /></a>\n<div>Peter Capaldi in excerpt from his video</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row" style="white-space: nowrap">Written by</th>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Peter_Capaldi" title="Peter Capaldi">Peter Capaldi</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row" style="white-space: nowrap">Original air date</th>\n<td>6 November 2014</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row" style="white-space: nowrap">Running time</th>\n<td>42 seconds</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>"<b>From The Doctor to my son Thomas</b>" is a <a href="/wiki/Viral_video" title="Viral video">viral video</a> recorded by actor <a href="/wiki/Peter_Capaldi" title="Peter Capaldi">Peter Capaldi</a> and sent to Thomas Goodall, an <a href="/wiki/Autism" title="Autism">autistic</a> nine-year-old boy in England, to console the child over grief from the death of Goodall\'s grandmother. Capaldi filmed the 42-second video in character as the <a href="/wiki/Twelfth_Doctor" title="Twelfth Doctor">12th incarnation</a> of <a href="/wiki/The_Doctor_(Doctor_Who)" title="The Doctor (Doctor Who)">The Doctor</a> in the <a href="/wiki/BBC" title="BBC">BBC</a> science-fiction series <i><a href="/wiki/Doctor_Who" title="Doctor Who">Doctor Who</a></i>. Capaldi\'s message had a positive effect on Thomas; his father said that the boy smiled for the first time since learning of his grandmother\'s death, and gained the courage to go to her funeral.</p>\n<p>Thomas\' father Ross Goodall posted the video to <a href="/wiki/YouTube" title="YouTube">YouTube</a> on 6 November 2014. He later explained to media that he wanted to make the video available to his family and had no idea it would become popular online. <a href="/wiki/CNN" title="CNN">CNN</a> reported that after its appearance on YouTube, the video was viewed over 200,000 times in its first 48 hours online. This more than doubled the next day, and less than a week later it had over 900,000 total views. <a href="/wiki/BBC_News" title="BBC News">BBC News</a> observed that Capaldi\'s message had become a viral video, and <i><a href="/wiki/ITV_News" title="ITV News">ITV News</a></i> described response to the video as a <a href="/wiki/Internet_phenomenon" class="mw-redirect" title="Internet phenomenon">global phenomenon</a>.</p>\n<p><i><a href="/wiki/The_Guardian" title="The Guardian">The Guardian</a></i> and <i><a href="/wiki/The_Daily_Telegraph" title="The Daily Telegraph">The Daily Telegraph</a></i> called the recording by Capaldi a touching video to a young child suffering from grief. CNN and <a href="/wiki/MTV" title="MTV">MTV</a> characterised the video similarly, as did Spanish and Dutch media. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Independent" title="The Independent">The Independent</a></i> wrote that Capaldi displayed a kinder face of his personality by sending the message. <a href="/wiki/BT_Group" title="BT Group">BT</a> commented it was Capaldi\'s best contribution as the character of the Doctor to date. The video had a positive impact on those with <a href="/wiki/Mental_health" title="Mental health">mental health</a> problems. <i>Autism Daily Newscast</i> reported favourably on the Doctor\'s actions. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Hollywood_Reporter" title="The Hollywood Reporter">The Hollywood Reporter</a></i> observed that as his character the Doctor, Capaldi was using his role to support mental health. <i><a href="/wiki/Hollywood_Life" title="Hollywood Life">Hollywood Life</a></i> said their reporters were moved to tears after watching Capaldi\'s video. <a href="/wiki/Peter_Harness" title="Peter Harness">Peter Harness</a>, writer of the episode "<a href="/wiki/Kill_the_Moon" title="Kill the Moon">Kill the Moon</a>", said that Capaldi\'s video was his favourite highlight from ten years of <i>Doctor Who</i>.</p>\n<p></p>\n<div id="toc" class="toc">\n<div class="toctitle">\n<h2>Contents</h2>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="#Background"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Background</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="#Prior_correspondence"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Prior correspondence</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-3"><a href="#Video_message"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">Video message</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-4"><a href="#Goodall_family_response"><span class="tocnumber">4</span> <span class="toctext">Goodall family response</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-5"><a href="#Posted_to_YouTube"><span class="tocnumber">5</span> <span class="toctext">Posted to YouTube</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-6"><a href="#Reception"><span class="tocnumber">6</span> <span class="toctext">Reception</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-7"><a href="#Impact"><span class="tocnumber">7</span> <span class="toctext">Impact</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-8"><a href="#See_also"><span class="tocnumber">8</span> <span class="toctext">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-9"><a href="#Footnotes"><span class="tocnumber">9</span> <span class="toctext">Footnotes</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-10"><a href="#References"><span class="tocnumber">10</span> <span class="toctext">References</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-11"><a href="#Further_reading"><span class="tocnumber">11</span> <span class="toctext">Further reading</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-12"><a href="#External_links"><span class="tocnumber">12</span> <span class="toctext">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<p></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Background">Background</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Background">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:172px;"><a href="/wiki/File:SDCC_2015_-_Peter_Capaldi_(19671457231)_cropped.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Peter Capaldi seated with microphone" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/SDCC_2015_-_Peter_Capaldi_%2819671457231%29_cropped.jpg/170px-SDCC_2015_-_Peter_Capaldi_%2819671457231%29_cropped.jpg" width="170" height="227" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/SDCC_2015_-_Peter_Capaldi_%2819671457231%29_cropped.jpg/255px-SDCC_2015_-_Peter_Capaldi_%2819671457231%29_cropped.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/SDCC_2015_-_Peter_Capaldi_%2819671457231%29_cropped.jpg/340px-SDCC_2015_-_Peter_Capaldi_%2819671457231%29_cropped.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1896" data-file-height="2528" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:SDCC_2015_-_Peter_Capaldi_(19671457231)_cropped.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\n<a href="/wiki/Peter_Capaldi" title="Peter Capaldi">Peter Capaldi</a> in 2015</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The Scottish actor and film director <a href="/wiki/Peter_Capaldi" title="Peter Capaldi">Peter Capaldi</a> was cast in 2013 as the <a href="/wiki/Twelfth_Doctor" title="Twelfth Doctor">12th incarnation</a> of the Doctor,<sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5">[a]</a></sup> in the BBC science-fiction series <i><a href="/wiki/Doctor_Who" title="Doctor Who">Doctor Who</a></i>. His casting was announced on 4 August 2013 in a special BBC programme hosted by <a href="/wiki/Zo%C3%AB_Ball" title="Zo\xc3\xab Ball">Zo\xc3\xab Ball</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6">[5]</a></sup> Capaldi first appeared as the Doctor in a cameo in the 50th anniversary special "<a href="/wiki/The_Day_of_the_Doctor" title="The Day of the Doctor">The Day of the Doctor</a>", before appearing in the 2013 Christmas special "<a href="/wiki/The_Time_of_the_Doctor" title="The Time of the Doctor">The Time of the Doctor</a>". A lifelong fan of the series, Capaldi had played Lobus Caecilius in the 2008 episode "<a href="/wiki/The_Fires_of_Pompeii" title="The Fires of Pompeii">The Fires of Pompeii</a>" and a civil servant, <a href="/wiki/John_Frobisher" class="mw-redirect" title="John Frobisher">John Frobisher</a>, in the 2009 spin-off <i><a href="/wiki/Torchwood:_Children_of_Earth" title="Torchwood: Children of Earth">Torchwood: Children of Earth</a></i>.<sup id="cite_ref-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-7">[6]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-8">[7]</a></sup></p>\n<p>Before taking the role, Capaldi said that he had to seriously consider the increased visibility that would come with the part.<sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-9">[8]</a></sup> He said in an interview with <i><a href="/wiki/Entertainment_Weekly" title="Entertainment Weekly">Entertainment Weekly</a></i> that he had been invited to audition for the role of the <a href="/wiki/Eighth_Doctor" title="Eighth Doctor">Eighth Doctor</a> in 1995 before the production of <a href="/wiki/Doctor_Who_(film)" title="Doctor Who (film)">the 1996 TV film</a>, but did not go because he was unsure if he would get the part and did not wish to be part of a large group of actors turned down for the role.<sup id="cite_ref-onceupon_10-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-onceupon-10">[9]</a></sup></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Prior_correspondence">Prior correspondence</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Prior correspondence">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Thomas Goodall, from <a href="/wiki/North_Baddesley" title="North Baddesley">North Baddesley</a> in <a href="/wiki/Hampshire" title="Hampshire">Hampshire</a>, had been a devoted fan of <i>Doctor Who</i> since the age of two and wrote a letter to Peter Capaldi saying he hoped the actor found success in his new role portraying the Doctor.<sup id="cite_ref-grinberg_11-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-grinberg-11">[10]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup> The Goodall family were all fans of <i>Doctor Who</i>, describing themselves as <a href="/wiki/Doctor_Who_fandom" title="Doctor Who fandom">Whovians</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-romseyadvertiser_13-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-romseyadvertiser-13">[12]</a></sup> Thomas decorated his home with objects related to the television series.<sup id="cite_ref-14" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-14">[13]</a></sup> Capaldi wrote back to Thomas thanking him, and sent a note to the child\'s father saying that he intended to send a video message.<sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup> Capaldi enclosed guidance to Ross Goodall on how to organise a tour of the production studios for <i>Doctor Who</i>.<sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup></p>\n<p>Ross Goodall subsequently communicated with Capaldi through the actor\'s agent, to inform him that Thomas\'s grandmother had died.<sup id="cite_ref-grinberg_11-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-grinberg-11">[10]</a></sup> (Helen, aged 72, died in early October 2014.<sup id="cite_ref-romseyadvertiser_13-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-romseyadvertiser-13">[12]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-bbcmundo_15-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-bbcmundo-15">[14]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-deredactie_16-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-deredactie-16">[15]</a></sup>) He told Capaldi that his son was not dealing well with the grief from his grandmother\'s death.<sup id="cite_ref-grinberg_11-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-grinberg-11">[10]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-washingtonpost_17-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-washingtonpost-17">[16]</a></sup> The family received the subsequent video message to Thomas from Capaldi three weeks after the death of the child\'s grandmother.<sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Video_message">Video message</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Video message">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Capaldi appears in character as the Doctor and addresses Thomas directly, greeting him by name.<sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-ibt_18-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ibt-18">[17]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-finbow_19-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-finbow-19">[18]</a></sup> He expresses his gratitude at receiving the child\'s letter, saying that it had pleased him.<sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-finbow_19-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-finbow-19">[18]</a></sup></p>\n<p>He then speaks to Thomas about grief, mentioning the Doctor\'s adventures with <a href="/wiki/Companion_(Doctor_Who)" title="Companion (Doctor Who)">travelling companion</a> <a href="/wiki/Clara_Oswald" title="Clara Oswald">Clara Oswald</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-alicevincent_20-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-alicevincent-20">[19]</a></sup> He tells Thomas that negative events impact Clara and himself in their journeys through the universe and <a href="/wiki/Time_travel" title="Time travel">time travel</a>, and that occasionally they feel depressed too.<sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-finbow_19-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-finbow-19">[18]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-mtv_21-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-mtv-21">[20]</a></sup> The Doctor tells Thomas that he is glad the child is supporting him in his adventures.<sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-finbow_19-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-finbow-19">[18]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-mtv_21-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-mtv-21">[20]</a></sup></p>\n<p>Capaldi concludes the video message by wishing Thomas to experience joy, and encourages the youth to be well and remain positive.<sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-ibt_18-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ibt-18">[17]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-finbow_19-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-finbow-19">[18]</a></sup> The video is 42 seconds long.<sup id="cite_ref-washingtonpost_17-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-washingtonpost-17">[16]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-gloucester_22-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-gloucester-22">[21]</a></sup></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Goodall_family_response">Goodall family response</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Goodall family response">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:172px;"><a href="/wiki/File:WPDW.png" class="image"><img alt="Doctor Who in lettering with blue police box graphic" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/92/WPDW.png/170px-WPDW.png" width="170" height="170" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/92/WPDW.png/255px-WPDW.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/92/WPDW.png/340px-WPDW.png 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:WPDW.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nThe boy referred to in the video by Capaldi was a devoted fan of the BBC television series <i><a href="/wiki/Doctor_Who" title="Doctor Who">Doctor Who</a></i>.<sup id="cite_ref-grinberg_11-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-grinberg-11">[10]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-washingtonpost_17-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-washingtonpost-17">[16]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-hollywoodreporter_23-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-hollywoodreporter-23">[22]</a></sup></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The family received the video from Capaldi on 3 November 2014.<sup id="cite_ref-grinberg_11-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-grinberg-11">[10]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-hollywoodreporter_23-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-hollywoodreporter-23">[22]</a></sup> After viewing the video, Thomas felt encouraged to attend his grandmother\'s funeral. In an interview with <i>The Guardian</i>, Ross Goodall explained that Capaldi\'s mention of sadness resonated with the child due to his experience of grief over his grandmother\'s death. He discussed the manner in which Thomas perceived emotions as a strict dichotomy between positive and negative without a middle ground. Thomas interpreted from the video that it was all right to feel happy while simultaneously acknowledging that a sad event had occurred. Ross Goodall told <i>The Guardian</i> that before viewing the video from Capaldi, his son had not wanted to attend the funeral.<sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup></p>\n<p>The boy\'s mother said that the video had helped him to deal with his depression.<sup id="cite_ref-radiotimes_24-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-radiotimes-24">[23]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-selby_25-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-selby-25">[24]</a></sup> After watching Capaldi\'s message, Ross Goodall stated that his son\'s behaviour patterns changed markedly. This change included the ability to comfort his sister and step out of his day-to-day routine.<sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-10" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup> Ross Goodall said that after watching the video, his son smiled for the first time since his grandmother\'s death.<sup id="cite_ref-grinberg_11-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-grinberg-11">[10]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-11" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup> The family framed the letter from Capaldi that came before the video message, and Ross Goodall said that Thomas looked at it when he felt distressed.<sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-12" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Posted_to_YouTube">Posted to YouTube</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Posted to YouTube">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Ross Goodall uploaded the message from Capaldi to the video-sharing website <a href="/wiki/YouTube" title="YouTube">YouTube</a> on 6 November 2014.<sup id="cite_ref-grinberg_11-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-grinberg-11">[10]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-13" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-alicevincent_20-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-alicevincent-20">[19]</a></sup> He commented at the video\'s YouTube location that he was surprised at the online response, and that at the time of initial posting was unaware it would <a href="/wiki/Viral_video" title="Viral video">become viral</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-selby_25-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-selby-25">[24]</a></sup> He later explained that he had uploaded it only to share it with family members on completion of the memorial services for Thomas\'s grandmother.<sup id="cite_ref-mashable_26-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-mashable-26">[25]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-bbccomforts_27-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-bbccomforts-27">[26]</a></sup> Thomas\'s father wrote that the video greatly affected his son, and enabled him to cope with grief and feel comforted.<sup id="cite_ref-selby_25-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-selby-25">[24]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-mtv_21-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-mtv-21">[20]</a></sup> He praised Capaldi for his kind act and explained that the video improved his son\'s mental well-being throughout the ordeal.<sup id="cite_ref-mtv_21-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-mtv-21">[20]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-selby_25-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-selby-25">[24]</a></sup></p>\n<p>By 10 November 2014, total comments by viewers posted below the video on YouTube numbered in the hundreds.<sup id="cite_ref-28" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-28">[27]</a></sup> The majority of comments were supportive. Visitors to the site wrote favourably of Capaldi\'s actions to record the video for the child. A few observed that Capaldi\'s version of the Doctor character is sinister and serious, and contrasted this with the actor\'s depiction of the character as warm and effusive in his recording.<sup id="cite_ref-ibt_18-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ibt-18">[17]</a></sup></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Reception">Reception</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Reception">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="quotebox" style="float: right; clear: right; margin: 0.5em 0 0.8em 1.4em; width:25em; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #aaa; font-size: 88%; background-color: #c6dbf7;">\n<div class="" style="position: relative; text-align: left;">\n<div>"...&#160;this unique performance may well be his most admirable adventure yet."</div>\n</div>\n<cite style="display: block; text-align: right;">&#160;\xe2\x80\x94<a href="/wiki/BT_Group" title="BT Group">BT</a><sup id="cite_ref-btgroup_29-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-btgroup-29">[28]</a></sup></cite></div>\n<p><a href="/wiki/CNN" title="CNN">CNN</a> reported that after its appearance on YouTube, the video had over 200,000 views in its first 48 hours of availability.<sup id="cite_ref-grinberg_11-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-grinberg-11">[10]</a></sup> <a href="/wiki/BBC_News" title="BBC News">BBC News</a> noted that by the next day, it had received over 500,000 views,<sup id="cite_ref-bbccomforts_27-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-bbccomforts-27">[26]</a></sup> and by 10 November 2014 it had over 750,000.<sup id="cite_ref-dailyecho_30-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-dailyecho-30">[29]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-hampshirechronicle_31-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-hampshirechronicle-31">[30]</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/The_Washington_Post" title="The Washington Post">The Washington Post</a></i> noted that by the next day the view count was above 900,000.<sup id="cite_ref-washingtonpost_17-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-washingtonpost-17">[16]</a></sup> Multiple publications observed that Capaldi\'s message had become a viral video.<sup id="cite_ref-bbcmundo_15-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-bbcmundo-15">[14]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-bbccomforts_27-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-bbccomforts-27">[26]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-timedwards_32-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-timedwards-32">[31]</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/ITV_News" title="ITV News">ITV News</a></i> called online reaction to the video a <a href="/wiki/Internet_phenomenon" class="mw-redirect" title="Internet phenomenon">global phenomenon</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-worldwidephenomenon_33-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-worldwidephenomenon-33">[32]</a></sup></p>\n<p><i><a href="/wiki/The_Guardian" title="The Guardian">The Guardian</a></i> called the recording by Capaldi a touching video tribute.<sup id="cite_ref-rawlinson_12-14" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-rawlinson-12">[11]</a></sup> CNN characterised the video similarly,<sup id="cite_ref-grinberg_11-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-grinberg-11">[10]</a></sup> as did <i><a href="/wiki/Digital_Spy" title="Digital Spy">Digital Spy</a></i>,<sup id="cite_ref-finbow_19-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-finbow-19">[18]</a></sup> <i>ITV News</i>,<sup id="cite_ref-34" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-34">[33]</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/TV_3_(Ireland)" class="mw-redirect" title="TV 3 (Ireland)">TV 3</a></i>,<sup id="cite_ref-35" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-35">[34]</a></sup> and publications in Spanish<sup id="cite_ref-bbcmundo_15-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-bbcmundo-15">[14]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-lavanguardia_36-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-lavanguardia-36">[35]</a></sup> and Dutch.<sup id="cite_ref-deredactie_16-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-deredactie-16">[15]</a></sup> The <a href="/wiki/Barcelona" title="Barcelona">Barcelona</a> newspaper <i><a href="/wiki/La_Vanguardia" title="La Vanguardia">La Vanguardia</a></i> wrote that Capaldi\'s video was an example of bringing joy into someone\'s life through a small act.<sup id="cite_ref-lavanguardia_36-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-lavanguardia-36">[35]</a></sup> <i>The Washington Post</i> called it a touching message.<sup id="cite_ref-washingtonpost_17-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-washingtonpost-17">[16]</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/The_Daily_Dot" title="The Daily Dot">The Daily Dot</a></i> described the video as inspirational.<sup id="cite_ref-aaronsankin_37-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-aaronsankin-37">[36]</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/The_Independent" title="The Independent">The Independent</a></i> contrasted Capaldi\'s portrayal of the <a href="/wiki/Twelfth_Doctor" title="Twelfth Doctor">12th Doctor</a> as one of the darker incarnations of the character with his kinder message as the same character in the video.<sup id="cite_ref-selby_25-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-selby-25">[24]</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/MTV" title="MTV">MTV</a></i> called Capaldi a most wonderful person for his act, and concluded that the video was quite endearing.<sup id="cite_ref-mtv_21-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-mtv-21">[20]</a></sup></p>\n<p><i><a href="/wiki/The_Daily_Telegraph" title="The Daily Telegraph">The Daily Telegraph</a></i> described the video as a moving inspiration to a child suffering from grief.<sup id="cite_ref-alicevincent_20-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-alicevincent-20">[19]</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/The_Huffington_Post" class="mw-redirect" title="The Huffington Post">The Huffington Post</a></i> wrote that if they were able to engage in time travel themselves, they would be unable to encounter a kinder tale.<sup id="cite_ref-huffington_38-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-huffington-38">[37]</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/Io9" title="Io9">Io9</a></i> appreciated that Capaldi was using his celebrity status to effect positive change through his portrayal of the character, and praised his use of the fictional role as a force for public good.<sup id="cite_ref-io9_39-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-io9-39">[38]</a></sup> The <i><a href="/wiki/South_Wales_Evening_Post" title="South Wales Evening Post">South Wales Evening Post</a></i> noted that Capaldi had appeared in a brief video as himself congratulating a bride on her wedding, and wrote that this video was more impressive than the previous appearance.<sup id="cite_ref-southwales_40-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-southwales-40">[39]</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/Metro_(British_newspaper)" title="Metro (British newspaper)">Metro</a></i> commented "Just when you thought Peter Capaldi couldn\'t possibly get any cooler, he\'s gone and outdone himself with this video."<sup id="cite_ref-westbrook_41-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-westbrook-41">[40]</a></sup></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Impact">Impact</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Impact">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><i><a href="/wiki/International_Business_Times" title="International Business Times">International Business Times</a></i> reported that the video message had a significant impact on the child, in spite of its brevity, and noted in a follow-up piece that Capaldi\'s video was featured in headlines of multiple newspapers.<sup id="cite_ref-ibt_18-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ibt-18">[17]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-42" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-42">[41]</a></sup> <i>Digital Spy</i> followed up on its earlier favourable coverage of Capaldi\'s video, and chose it as the number one entry out of "7 awesome celebrity moments that will melt your heart".<sup id="cite_ref-43" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-43">[42]</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/Hollywood_Life" title="Hollywood Life">Hollywood Life</a></i> said that their journalists were moved to tears after watching the video. Their review concluded that Capaldi\'s message was both kind and strong, and that it was intelligent of the actor to compare the grief of Thomas to that encountered by his character on the television programme.<sup id="cite_ref-hollywoodlife_44-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-hollywoodlife-44">[43]</a></sup></p>\n<p>Capaldi\'s actions received favourable coverage from the <i>Autism Daily Newscast</i>, an official Google News website reporting on current events and news of interest to those on the autism spectrum,<sup id="cite_ref-autismdaily_45-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-autismdaily-45">[44]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-46" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-46">[45]</a></sup> with site journalist Jo Worgan noting that the actor had devoted himself while on the set of <i>Doctor Who</i> to spending time with an autistic girl who was a fan of the show.<sup id="cite_ref-autismdaily_45-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-autismdaily-45">[44]</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/The_Hollywood_Reporter" title="The Hollywood Reporter">The Hollywood Reporter</a></i> noted that the <a href="/wiki/Time_Lord" title="Time Lord">Time Lord</a> character took time to support the mental well-being of a child in addition to his duties of protecting the universe from harm.<sup id="cite_ref-hollywoodreporter_23-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-hollywoodreporter-23">[22]</a></sup></p>\n<p>In a March 2015 interview with <i><a href="/wiki/Radio_Times" title="Radio Times">Radio Times</a></i>, <a href="/wiki/Peter_Harness" title="Peter Harness">Peter Harness</a>, writer of <i>Doctor Who</i> episode "<a href="/wiki/Kill_the_Moon" title="Kill the Moon">Kill the Moon</a>", cited the video by Capaldi as his favourite highlight from the last ten years of the television programme. Harness explained his decision, saying that the video demonstrated Capaldi\'s kind demeanour and illustrated that <i>Doctor Who</i> served to assist youngsters in learning about the travails of greater society. He said that, by extension, it reminded all viewers to act with more compassion towards one another.<sup id="cite_ref-mulkern_47-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-mulkern-47">[46]</a></sup></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="See_also">See also</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: See also">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role="navigation" aria-label="Portals" class="noprint portal plainlist tright" style="margin:0.5em 0 0.5em 1em;border:solid #aaa 1px">\n<ul style="display:table;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0.1em;max-width:175px;background:#f9f9f9;font-size:85%;line-height:110%;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold">\n<li style="display:table-row"><span style="display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:TARDIS-trans.png" class="image"><img alt="icon" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bb/TARDIS-trans.png/20px-TARDIS-trans.png" width="20" height="28" class="noviewer" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bb/TARDIS-trans.png/30px-TARDIS-trans.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bb/TARDIS-trans.png/40px-TARDIS-trans.png 2x" data-file-width="635" data-file-height="889" /></a></span><span style="display:table-cell;padding:0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em;vertical-align:middle"><a href="/wiki/Portal:Doctor_Who" title="Portal:Doctor Who">Doctor Who portal</a></span></li>\n<li style="display:table-row"><span style="display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:Crystal_Clear_app_linneighborhood.svg" class="image"><img alt="icon" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f9/Crystal_Clear_app_linneighborhood.svg/28px-Crystal_Clear_app_linneighborhood.svg.png" width="28" height="28" class="noviewer" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f9/Crystal_Clear_app_linneighborhood.svg/42px-Crystal_Clear_app_linneighborhood.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f9/Crystal_Clear_app_linneighborhood.svg/56px-Crystal_Clear_app_linneighborhood.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="407" data-file-height="407" /></a></span><span style="display:table-cell;padding:0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em;vertical-align:middle"><a href="/wiki/Portal:Internet" title="Portal:Internet">Internet portal</a></span></li>\n<li style="display:table-row"><span style="display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:Autism-stacking-cans_2nd_edit.jpg" class="image"><img alt="icon" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Autism-stacking-cans_2nd_edit.jpg/20px-Autism-stacking-cans_2nd_edit.jpg" width="20" height="28" class="noviewer" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Autism-stacking-cans_2nd_edit.jpg/31px-Autism-stacking-cans_2nd_edit.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Autism-stacking-cans_2nd_edit.jpg/41px-Autism-stacking-cans_2nd_edit.jpg 2x" data-file-width="409" data-file-height="559" /></a></span><span style="display:table-cell;padding:0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em;vertical-align:middle"><a href="/wiki/Portal:Pervasive_developmental_disorders" title="Portal:Pervasive developmental disorders">Pervasive developmental disorders portal</a></span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Doctor_Who_(series_8)" title="Doctor Who (series 8)"><i>Doctor Who</i> (series 8)</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Global_perceptions_of_autism" title="Global perceptions of autism">Global perceptions of autism</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Sociological_and_cultural_aspects_of_autism" title="Sociological and cultural aspects of autism">Sociological and cultural aspects of autism</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Whoniverse" title="Whoniverse">Whoniverse</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Footnotes">Footnotes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Footnotes">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">\n<div class="mw-references-wrap">\n<ol class="references">\n<li id="cite_note-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Within the series\' narrative, the Doctor is a <a href="/wiki/Time_travel" title="Time travel">time travelling</a>, <a href="/wiki/Humanoid" title="Humanoid">humanoid</a> <a href="/wiki/Extraterrestrial_life" title="Extraterrestrial life">alien</a> from a race known as the <a href="/wiki/Time_Lords" class="mw-redirect" title="Time Lords">Time Lords</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-markbould_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-markbould-1">[1]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-essential_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-essential-2">[2]</a></sup> When the Doctor is critically injured, he can <a href="/wiki/Regeneration_(Doctor_Who)" title="Regeneration (Doctor Who)">regenerate</a> his body, and in doing so gain a new physical appearance, and with it a distinct new personality; this plot mechanism has allowed the Doctor to be portrayed by a series of actors over the decades since the programme\'s inception in 1963.<sup id="cite_ref-leebarron_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-leebarron-3">[3]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-orlebar_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-orlebar-4">[4]</a></sup></span></li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="References">References</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=From_The_Doctor_to_my_son_Thomas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: References">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="reflist columns references-column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;">\n<ol class="references">\n<li id="cite_note-markbould-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-markbould_1-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book">Bould, Mark; Butler, Andrew; Roberts, Adam; et al., eds. (2010). "The Doctor (1963-)". <i>Fifty Key Figures in Science Fiction</i>. Routledge. pp.&#160;71\xe2\x80